						Gleb has 20 years of investment management, brokerage and custody experience in Russia. <br><br>
						Before joining ITI Funds Gleb served as Managing Director at ITI Capital (former ITinvest), where he also oversaw the trading desk, financing operations, and investment banking services. <br><br>
						He moved to ITI Capital from Renaissance Capital, where he led the development of structured and other investment products in 2009 and served as CEO in 2010-2012. In 2008 Gleb was managing director at Da Vinci Capital responsible for the development of equity funds. Previously Gleb had experience as manager of event driven hedge fund, CEO at Renaissance Broker, Head of Custody in Credit Suisse.
					</div>
				</div>

